,Recommended,244030,28699657,"Posted: 26 December, 2016",all,TechStudios,"Love this game and totally recommend it! First - don't get fooled by the bad reviews. They complain about bugs, slow performence, etc.First off, this game isn't released. You need to accept that.. some of the bugs are actually really, really fun and cool. Though, the game is in early access. I would seriously hate for the game to go down, but I don't think it will. :)Take on Mars is very realistic and a REALLY, REALLY good Sandbox game. The campaign so far is really good. There's an awesome editor mode for making your own scenarios (and just for awesome role play), kind of like Arma III. I love that!The space and planet mechanics work great. Not in an equally pressurized place with no oxygen? Your oxygen in your lunges gets forced out of your mouth and you eventually die, unless you are smart and have a space suit on.There's an awesome damage system, meaning you can crack your helmet and break a big component of your suit, and it takes lots of your oxygen away and lowers the duration and time you got left till you run out of oxygen.The gravity in the game is also very realistic. If you are in an edit mode and go on the moon, you'd always want to jump around and see how high you can get in the air. Though, if you're in space, such as in the International Space Station or a little rocket ship, and you jump out, you probably won't be able to control where you are going due to gravity. This means that you're probably going to float away. You can avoid it by exiting your station/vehicle in space, but stay very, very close to it. For extra security, I hold down ""E"" to grab it. Then if you want, you can learn how to use a thruster pack thingy to thrust yourself back.There's a variety of space suits and vehicles to choose from, in which is a BIG bonus to the developers. Example, heavy space suits have more oxygen due to longer EVA sessions.In the editor mode, you may feel bored.. but then you just need to try things, such as placing a manned landing rocket thingy in the air, and watch as it falls and land on Mars, then step out and do whatever you want. I usually make up my story as I go in the editor mode.. that is what is fun about it.Then there are also robotic stuff, like landers and rovers that you can actually be in the campaign/edit mode. It's fun to mess around with that. Anyways, there are some bugs in the game. If you come across one, don't just quit and refund the game. Enjoy that it is a really cool game and in early access. Some bugs are fun to mess with! That's something to do if you're bored. Just.. don't get too crazy with them.Overall, great realistic sandbox space game! So far, the best space game I've ever played yet. I hope to see this game thrive and release in the future.==========================================Don't get overwhelmed by the bad reviews. I read all the bad reviews, bought the game, and totally had a blast! And I am still having a blast. :POverall rating: 10/10Good job devs!"
