,Not Recommended,244030,32194471,Posted: 5 June,all,ゆかり,"I have wasted 477 hours of my life on this thing.477 hours.I don't blame it for that. You could say a game's quality is measured by how many otherwise productive hours it can steal from you. Right and wrong on this one. A word for every fifteen minutes, shall we?Quick verdict: Excellent idea, rushed by the studio fairly wanting it to finally ship after five years in EA, after the developers fallen to the ruinous siren song of feature creep. If I bought this for its early access price of 14USD today, I'd dislike its lack of polish, and might refund it. At 27USD? Giddouttahere!Pros: The Mars terrains are really quite pretty, with the exception of Lyot Crater, which is nothing but repetitive dunes. The rovers look neat and are fully physically simulated in terms of joints, suspension, etc. and have lots of breakable things that can *and will* break if you don't avoid obstacles.Cons: Manned is janky. If you felt like a clumsy robot in an ArmA game? It's worse here. That clumsy robot is hamfisted into an engine originally for an RTS and is wearing a space suit in somewhat confined spaces. There's little in way of actual science, despite how the trailer keeps saying that. Construction is hard and unrewarding. No dedicated server support. Unmanned campaign feels neglected. Replayable help info replaced by videos that play only once that were, for some godforsaken reason, recorded while the game was in holiday mode with Christmas trees and lights everywhere.3/10, at this price point. 4 or 5 at the price I bought it. Do not recommend.In this link is the rest of the review. Read if you want, I guess. I'm gonna spoil everything, but you really won't missing out on much."
