76561197986370677,Recommended,244030,15731737,"Posted: 7 May, 2015",all,Hyenaz,"This is a revised review, after many patches.The good:- Many diverse game modes. And I do mean very diverse.- Decent modding support and capabilities.- One of the few games that does give you that old ""hard-SF"" space vibe. Its a nerdy game abotu space, which feels very refreshign after 100s of ""flashy"" fiction games on the topiuc of space exploration.- A decent survival game with resource extracting and base building etc, somewhat minecraft-style, but more rigid and more serious.The bad:- The game's physics engine is rough around the edges. When it works its great (does  aphenomenal job of simulating very low gravity on the moon for example). But at times you find yourself tripping over a cable in earth or mars gravity and the physics engine glitches and sends you flying 10 meters into the sky. These sort of physics glitches are annoying.- Its a ""take it slow"" game, not everyone's cup of tea. This might appeal more to pleople who play simulator games than to those who prefer action games. Both the manned and unmanned parts of the game- Shady and inconsistent OS support, something I really need to complain about. When I purchased the game, the Bohemia Interactive site listed ""Windows XP / Windows 7 / Vista"" in the Reccomended settings.  Now on steam its just Windows 7 and Vista. XP support seems to have been silently dropped and I feel somewhat cheated, as I was not able to play the game for a long time until I upgraded my PC and got a new Windows.- Some of the textures look a bit dated, though it has to be said that nice lighting and post-processing does a great job at covering this up."
