,Recommended,244030,9543631,"Posted: 18 March, 2014",all,wobbler,"Can't fault this game in any way really.It does exactly what it says on the tin and more besides.With the manned mission coming, it shows nothing but bigger and better things on the horizon.And the best thing of all is that I can honestly say this has been the best experience of early access development I have encountered ever.Mostly it's just an occasional update. Sometimes it's a game released as a tech demo and then the devs vanish with your cash. Other times they release a couple of tiny updates that do nothing much, then call the game finished.These guys have been incredible, with a huge amount of updates, constant feedback on the forums, both here and the bohemia forums.I have even had them add me as a friend, ask for my input personally, and seen my suggestions added within a day.I have had them reply to a problem I was having, email my save file to one of them (Dram, he is just the best, seriously, great developer for early access, he is into helping the community all the time), and had a patch released that fixes a problem that only I was having. He did that within 2 hours of me posting the topic on the steam forum.As for the game. If you have any interest in this kind of thing, then this is for you. It does exactly what you would expect, and it does it in such a way as to make you feel like you work for NASA, without having to learn all about rocket science and such to do so.This alongside kerbal space program show exactly how this kind of game is great for early access, when they have the right developer.I can't fault this game at all.The only thing is that I am itching for release now, to see how the finished product turns out. But with all the new things they keep announcing, it looks likely to be in early access for a while.But seeing as the early access experience here has been almost as enjoyable as the game itself, I don't see that as a terrible thing. I have been made to feel important, an integral part of the evolution of the game, right from the start. And their enthusiasm hasn't waned at all.Buy it, buy it now, even if just to support early access done right."
