,Recommended,244030,20859173,"Posted: 30 January, 2016",all,Rydogdav,"Sooooooo, I'm just gonna say it now: in this game you ""have to science the s**t out of this"". Besides the ability to completely reinact the entirity of The Martian, the game is really awesome and in-depth. You start out with a few vehicles and your trusty 3D Printer. Enter Mars- The Red, Dead, Planet. Get out while it's light and get to work: place the foundations of your base, get some solar panels and some ""boxes of doom"" (if you haven't guessed it yet, I'm going to be quoting The Martian a bit) down, and then get to bed in your spawn vehicle so you don't freeze to death when night falls. In all seriousness, this game is truely a sandbox game. Go anywhere within the map (consisting of real life landmarks/landscapes of Mars) place anything (implemented) in the game, harvest, refine, print, repeat. And its not even a full freaking game yet! (If I haven't sold you, either something's wrong with you, or you just hate The Martian)In the great words of Shia LaBeouf: JUST [BUY] IT!!!"
