,Not Recommended,244030,9977086,"Posted: 29 April, 2014",all,nannerpuss,"This was a positive review, but I no longer feel that way. Ammended review:It's been in Early Access for (literally) years now. At some point it becomes an excuse for developers to never finish something, or always be able to promise ""more features in the future"" - which is what's happened here.I was severely disappointed several months ago when I realized they no longer cared about science results and testing of Mars and started focusing on the multiplayer aspect, but I know teenagers/gamers are the target audience on Steam, so I wasn't completely surprised by the shift. However, that was nearly a year ago. In that time, nothing has changed in the single-player ""science"" campaign at all. It's been the same thing since I bought the game years ago. I really, really wanted to like this game, but it's just not meant to be. I mean, how long can you call something ""beta"", yet make money from it, and get away with it?If Bohemia can own up to the failures and shortcomings and put some TLC (ie. patching, time, development, and customer concern awareness) back into this, I might switch back to a positive review. But that is very doubtful at this point. They've run out of time for me."
